  "prompt": "I got 168 in JEE (Main) 2016. How much score should I expect (rough range) according to my potential , in BITSAT 2016 ?",
  "response": "The score in JEE (Main) doesn't directly correlate to the score you can expect in BITSAT, as both exams differ in structure, subject emphasis, and difficulty. However, we can provide a rough estimate based on general trends.\n\nGiven that you scored 168 in JEE (Main) 2016, which is fairly decent, you might expect a BITSAT score in the range of 210 to 250. Many students who perform well in JEE (Main) tend to score similarly in BITSAT but bear in mind that BITSAT also has sections on logical reasoning and a specific emphasis on speed and accuracy.\n\nPlease remember that preparation and familiarity with the exam format are crucial as BITSAT has a different pattern and the computer-based format. It's always best to take mock tests and practice previous years' papers specifically for BITSAT to get a more accurate measure of your potential score.",
